	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">baisoku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">[Tearing] will not happen on a raster console like NES and TV, because the image is being output in lock-step with the electron beam of the CRT</div>
<br />Unless you're dealing with a bad upscaler, such as the one in a cheap HDTV CRT or a multi-system CRT that converts from 240p/480i to 480p or from PAL to NTSC. They may trip up on the non-standard 60.099 Hz refresh rate of the NES and display a minute amount of tearing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
